h.test.ts > getUniversalSearchResults > queue_event_id identifier (short numeric): only fires the queue lookup for numeric queries and shapes the row\nAssertionError: expected [] to have a length of 1 but got +0\n\n\u001b[32m- Expected\u001b[39m\n\u001b[31m+ Received\u001b[39m\n\n\u001b[32m- 1\u001b[39m\n\u001b[31m+ 0\u001b[39m\n\n ❯ src/server/db/queries/__tests__/universal-search.test.ts:395:25\n    393|     expect(response.queryClass).toBe(\"queue_event_id\");\n    394|     const qe = response.groups.find((g) => g.entityType === \"queue_eve…\n    395|     expect(qe?.results).toHaveLength(1);\n       |                         ^\n    396|     expect(qe?.results[0].id).toBe(\"777\");\n    397|     expect(qe?.results[0].label).toBe(\"#777\");\n\n⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯[4/4]⎯\n\n\n Test Files  1 failed | 22 passed (23)\n      Tests  4 failed | 169 passed (173)\n   Start at  11:44:13\n   Duration  25.52s (transform 2.08s, setup 12.66s, collect 15.77s, tests 3.63s, environment 88.24s, prepare 12.08s)\n\n ELIFECYCLE  Test failed. See above for more details.","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
